    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="59"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/154–156.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 735.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 1244, of the 28th ultimo, inclosing a printed copy and translation
                    of an excerpt <pb facs="0777" n="627" xml:id="pg_627"/> from the final act of
                    dissolution of the Central American Arbitral Tribunal, dated San Salvador,
                    February 8, 1907, and a copy and translation of an excerpt from a telegram sent
                    by President Zelaya to Mr. Anderson, Costa Rican minister for foreign relations,
                    dated the 18th ultimo, stating that he (President Zelaya) has the moral support
                    of the President of the United States in making war upon Honduras.</p>
                <p>On the 15th instant the department sent you the following telegram, which I now
                        confirm:<note n="a" xml:id="d59fna">Supra.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The same telegram was also sent, on the same date, to the American chargé
                    d’affaires ad interim at Tegucigalpa.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
